INSERT INTO `news` VALUES (2,'Peace FM Report on ARIS Samsung Room','2014-november-peace-fm-report-on-aris-samsung-room','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2014/december/peace-fm-feature.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"470\" height=\"264\" /></p><p>Technology giant, Samsung Electronics West Africa (SEWA) has introduced its first Samsung School education solution to the Al Rayan International School, East-Legon.</p><p>The solution integrates an array of Samsung devices with interactive software to impart knowledge in students. Components of the Samsung School solution are Samsung-powered e-boards, server, Samsung tablets, wifi access point and a wifi printer</p><p><a href=\"http://news.peacefmonline.com/pages/tech/201412/224983.php\">Read the rest</a></p>','Technology giant, Samsung Electronics West Africa (SEWA) has introduced its first Samsung School education solution to the Al Rayan International School, East-Legon.The solution integrates an array of Samsung devices wit...','2014-11-19 18:57:24','2015-02-21 18:51:17','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2014-12-08 00:00:00'),(3,'Samsung Smart School in ARIS','2014-november-samsung-smart-school-in-aris','/img/uploads/2014/november/akwaba-annette-austin.jpg','<p>A video report on ARIS being the first school in Ghana to implement the Samsung Smart School platform</p><div class=\"videoWrapper\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wi6NFVl6UK8\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>','A video report on ARIS being the first school in Ghana to implement the Samsung Smart School platform','2014-11-19 18:59:58','2015-02-10 21:17:54','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2014-12-10 00:00:00'),(15,'What are the beliefs and values that drive the PYP ?','2015-february-what-are-the-beliefs-and-values-that-drive-the-pyp','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/february/values-beliefs.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"431\" height=\"281\" /></p><p>In the PYP, it is believed that learning takes place best when it is connected to what is genuinely a component of the world around the student, not merely what is all too often contrived and then im- posed upon the student in school; that the acquisition of knowledge and skills and the search for meaning and understanding are best done in the context of the exploration of relevant content. PYP schools should provide students with learning experiences that are engaging, relevant, challenging and significant, in learning environments that are stimulating and provocative, where:</p><ul><li>adults are sensitive facilitators of the process of empowering students to value their learning and to take responsibility for it</li><li>students are seen as competent and are listened to</li><li>students are encouraged to be curious, be inquisitive, ask questions, explore and interact with the environment physically, socially and intellectually</li><li>explicit learning outcomes and the learning process are made transparent to the students</li><li>students are supported in their struggle for mastery and control on their journey to become in- dependent, autonomous learners</li><li>the learning experiences are differentiated to accommodate the range of abilities and learning styles in the group</li><li>the collaboration on the part of all the PYP teachers is high, and there is a commitment to the transdisciplinary model at the core of this programme of international education.</li></ul>','In the PYP, it is believed that learning takes place best when it is connected to what is genuinely a component of the world around the student, not merely what is all too often contrived and then im- posed upon the stud...','2015-02-07 12:40:02','2015-02-21 18:50:38','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2015-01-07 00:00:00'),(16,'Black Holes, an Al-Rayan Project','2015-february-black-holes-an-al-rayan-project','','<p>Al-Rayan students Mouayad Toutoung (Year 11) and Bashhar Byrouthy (Year 10) produced a stirring video about black holes, as a community service in connection with the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ghanaplanetarium\">Ghana Planetarium</a>.</p><p>The young men are members of the Astronomical Society of Ghana..</p><div class=\"videoWrapper\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/T9nArucCJzc\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>','Al-Rayan students Mouayad Toutoung (Year 11) and Bashhar Byrouthy (Year 10) produced a stirring video about black holes, as a community service in connection with the Ghana Planetarium.The young men are members of the As...','2015-02-07 12:41:30','2015-02-12 10:26:43','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2015-01-07 00:00:00'),(17,'Lincoln CAS trips with students from ARIS','2015-february-lincoln-cas-trips-with-students-from-aris','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2014/december/lcs_aris_cover.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"471\" height=\"278\" /></p><p>The LCS CAS program has taken service learning to another level by engaging a fellow IB school in Ghana on their CAS trips. The new initiative connects students from the two schools in joint CAS trips and encourages them to fundraise together towards a common goal.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"http://www.lincoln.edu.gh/page.cfm?p=487&amp;newsid=911\">Read the rest</a></p>','The LCS CAS program has taken service learning to another level by engaging a fellow IB school in Ghana on their CAS trips. The new initiative connects students from the two schools in joint CAS trips and encourages them...','2015-02-10 21:24:16','2015-02-21 18:50:56','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2014-12-12 00:00:00'),(18,'Accepting Disability: The School That Made All The Difference','2015-february-accepting-disability-the-school-that-made-all-the-difference','','<p><em><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/january/modern_ghana_logo.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"219\" height=\"114\" /></em></p><p><em>Modern Ghana</em> reports:</p><p>No institution worth its sort would turn a blind eye to a very compelling social responsibility which, hitherto, has been neglected or forgotten for the want of a softer statement to aptly put it. However, it is quite obfuscating to find out how apathetic society is towards the physically challenged and that is easily read in the general lack of provisions made in all aspects of life.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.modernghana.com/news/591052/1/accepting-disability-the-school-that-made-all-the-.html\">Read the rest</a></p>','Modern Ghana reports:No institution worth its sort would turn a blind eye to a very compelling social responsibility which, hitherto, has been neglected or forgotten for the want of a softer statement to aptly put it. Ho...','2015-02-10 21:27:29','2015-02-21 18:50:18','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2015-01-09 00:00:00'),(19,'â€‹LCS collaborates with ARIS and National Forestry Commission to preserve wildlife','2015-february-lcs-collaborates-with-aris-and-national-forestry-commission-to-preserve-wildlife','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/january/aris_linconln_collaboration.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p><p>LCS teachers, Barbara Bilgre and Eric Boateng, are spearheading a wildlife and environmental preservation project with their students in collaboration with the Forestry Commission of Ghana and Al Rayyan International School (ARIS), another IB school in Accra.</p><p>LCS CAS students will be partnering with ARIS CAS students on this community development project for the Solo Monkey Forest, as well as on smaller service projects.</p><p>Students from the two schools met at ARIS premises in East Legon for their first meeting to discuss the proposed monkey sanctuary initiative.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.lincoln.edu.gh/page.cfm?p=487&amp;newsid=934&amp;ncat=3\">Read the rest</a></p>','LCS teachers, Barbara Bilgre and Eric Boateng, are spearheading a wildlife and environmental preservation project with their students in collaboration with the Forestry Commission of Ghana and Al Rayyan International Sch...','2015-02-10 21:40:22','2015-02-21 18:50:03','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2015-01-30 00:00:00'),(20,'Visit to Silver Star Automotives as Part of Unit of Inquiry','2015-february-visit-to-silver-star-automotives-as-part-of-unit-of-inquiry','','<h3>How we Organize ourselves</h3><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Central Idea:</strong></span> Communities make effort to create transportation systems to meet their needs.</p><p>(details after photos)</p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/february/mercedes-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/february/mercedes-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/february/wara-malek.png\" alt=\"\" /></p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/february/mercedes-4.png\" alt=\"\" /></p><p><strong>Features of transportation, decisions involved in using transportation and how systems of transportation respond to changing needs</strong> are the <strong>lines of inquiry</strong> year one students where inquiring about. Questions arose about do we get from one place to another? What are the different types of transportation experienced? These provocations provided students with a solid grounding for inquiring into the types of transport communities develop and how the needs of a community can influence the mode of transport within the community.</p><p>Throughout the unit, we had the opportunity to inquire into a system that has evolved into a range of ways overtime and varies across locations. They inquired into transport on land, sea and air for both people and cargo. Moreover, they further visited Silver Star Motors. The purpose was acquainting themselves with the various types of vehicles. They watched video presentations on the process of making of Mercedes Benz, cars and trucks. Moreover, We invited <a href=\"http://ghana.westafrican-rescue.com/\">WARA</a> to our campus and a paramedic explained to students the procedures in taking care of a sick or wounded person. Learners were exposed to the ambulance and inspected the different parts and tools; nevertheless asked lots of questions they were wondering about.</p><p><a href=\"http://silverstar.com.gh/News-And-Events/Local/A-Visit-by-Al-Rayaan-International-School.aspx\">More at&nbsp;Silver Star\'s website</a></p>','How we Organize ourselvesCentral Idea: Communities make effort to create transportation systems to meet their needs.(details after photos)Features of transportation, decisions involved in using transportation and how sys...','2015-02-13 19:35:32','2015-02-21 18:49:43','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2015-02-13 00:00:00');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `news` ENABLE KEYS */;
