INSERT INTO `people` VALUES (1,'Fatma','Odaymat','Principal','<p><img src =\"/img/uploads/pages/dr-odaymat.jpg\"></p>','Administration','2015-02-21 15:44:03','2015-02-21 15:44:03','','Dr.',1),(3,'Larry','Aidoo','Physical Education (PE) Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-025.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Larry Aidoo is a graduate teacher from the University of Education, Winneba, with a specialization in Physical Education and Sports. He has had seven years of teaching experience in public and international schools and is the Coordinator for the Primary and Secondary schools&rsquo; PE and Sports.</p>\r\n<p>He organises matches/competitions and serves as the Athletics and Basketball coach. Larry&rsquo;s teaching philosophy entails a strong belief that students learn through play; as youngsters play they enhance their knowledge, acquire new and improve existing skills. Introducing aspects of games and sports to young learners enhances their abilities and enriches their aspirations, both sporting and academic.</p>\r\n<p>The PE and Sports programmes aim to see students exploring higher tactical skills to generate an environment of sportsmanship and general well-being.</p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 19:46:02','2015-02-21 19:46:02','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(4,'Cindy','Benshab','French Coordinator and Teacher','<p>Cindy is an enthusiastic and passionate teacher at Al-Rayan International School. She joined it in 2012 and started as a French teacher to become the French Coordinator and teacher of secondary school. She holds two Bachelors&rsquo; degrees: one in languages, literature and foreign civilizations and one in linguistic studies from Paris Diderot University. She has also gained an IT management Diploma.</p>\r\n<p>Cindy is French and loves everything that has to do with French; the language itself, the culture and the food (of course). When she is teaching about France, she cannot help but make her students travel with their imagination and visit the monuments or eat a &lsquo;macaron&rsquo; at Ladur&eacute;e (French Bakery).</p>\r\n<p>When she is not teaching she loves going out with her friends, playing with her pets and shopping.</p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 21:32:05','2015-02-21 21:32:05','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Ms.',0),(5,'Mansur','Abubakar','Mathemathics Teacher','<p>Mansur Abubakar is an experienced teacher, who is able to establish and communicate clear objectives for all learning activities and develop high quality schemes of work and lesson plans for pupils. Combining these core competencies, and CIE training for teaching and marking IGCSE Mathematics and Physics, have made him an excellent educator.</p>\r\n<p>Mansur has been a Physics teacher since September 2005 in different countries. He earned his Bachelor of Science degree in Mathematics/Physics in 2004 and a Masters in 2013. He has a long and successful experience in teaching, as well as conducting research in the field of education.</p>\r\n<p>With his previous employer, where he worked for five years, he was renowned for being able to motivate, mobilize, and coach his students to achieve the highest academic levels. He taught the best CIE Mathematics students in 2013 and 2014, with total marks of 97% and 98% respectively. He can easily work with others in a professional manner while sharing a common goal. He also considers himself to be someone whose strengths include cultural sensitivity and an ability, in a multicultural setting, to build rapport with a diverse workforce.</p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 21:34:21','2015-02-21 21:34:21','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(6,'Edward','Appiah','Laboratory Technician','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-010.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\n\n<p>Edward Appiah is the Secondary Schoolâ€™s Laboratory Technician. He was born in Accra in May 1989 and attended Accra High School, where he excelled as a student.</p>\n\n<p>Edward received a Higher National Diploma (HND) in Laboratory Technology in August 2013, while studying at the Accra Polytechnic. </p>\n\n<p>Undertaking his national service at the Ghana Atomic Energy Commission, from September 2013 to August 2014, he took part in industrial research and gained experience in data collection and sample analysis. </p>\n\n<p>For his hobbies Edward likes to watch sci-fi movies, listen to music and read books.</p>','Staff','2015-02-21 21:37:45','2015-02-21 21:37:45','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(7,'Majida','Beiruti','Arabic as a Foreign Language (AFL) Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-003.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Since 2005, Majida Beiruti has been the Religious Education teacher and coordinator at ARIS. She became an Arabic as a Foreign Language (AFL) teacher for the Secondary level students in 2013.</p>\r\n<p>Majida was part of the ARIS curriculum committee for several years and played a major role in organizing and managing the daily assemblies as well. She taught PSHE for more than 7 years, moral education (through drama) for more than eight years, and has been chosen as Teacher of the Year on two occasions.</p>\r\n<p>Heading the Daawah Committee women&rsquo;s section for four years, for 13 years she has also been an active member with the Ghana Society for Islamic Education and Reformation (GSIER). Majida always challenges herself into being constructive and innovative. One thing about her, is that one cannot see her in the morning without her mug of coffee and throughout the day without her smile.</p>\r\n<p>When she is free, she likes to read, to watch movies and cook.</p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 21:43:51','2015-02-21 21:43:51','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Ms.',0),(8,'Stephen','Bobila','Mathemathics Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-002.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Stephen Bobila gained admission to the University of Ghana, Legon, to read for a Bachelor of Arts degree, combining Mathematics, Computer Science, Economics and Statistics. He graduated in Mathematics with Statistics.</p>\r\n<p>After graduation, he was recruited by the university&rsquo;s Head of Mathematics Department to fulfil the National Service requirement with the department, lecturing Level 200 students and conducting tutorials with Level 100 and 300 students.</p>\r\n<p>In 2013 he joined ARIS, where he is currently teaching Extended and Additional Mathematics for the International General Certificate of Secondary Education (IGCSE).</p>\r\n<p>One of his favourite quotes is by Shakuntala Devi: &ldquo;Without mathematics, there&rsquo;s nothing you can do. Everything around you is mathematics. Everything around you is numbers.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Stephen believes that mathematics is not just about finding the value of &ldquo;&ldquo;in the classroom context, but also involves applying how you obtained the &ldquo;&ldquo;value to your everyday activities and in solving everyday problems.</p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 21:47:49','2015-02-21 21:47:49','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(9,'Manelle','Boudjema','Arabic Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-018.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Mrs Manelle Boudjema was born in Algeria. A teacher of Arabic, she has a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Clinical Psychology from Mentouri University of Constantine, Algeria, from which she graduated in 2000.</p>\r\n<p>Manelle is married with two children. She likes reading, and is fascinated by news, current affairs and world events. She has been attracted to the teaching profession since she was young and, like her father, has always aspired to be a teacher.</p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 21:53:06','2015-02-21 21:53:06','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Ms.',0),(10,'Kobena','Brew','IGCSE Economics, Enterprise and Business Studies Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-012.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Born in the mid 80&rsquo;s to a Ghanaian musician/cultural ambassador and a British nurse, Kobena Brew started his primary education in the Morning Star School in Accra, where he received his Basic Education Certificate.</p>\r\n<p>He proceeded to gain his Senior High School Certificate at the Mfantsipim School, where he was elected a member of the school prefectural board in his final year. He then moved to the UK where he gained admission into Wiltshire College, Trowbridge, followed by Bournemouth University, where he attained his Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Business and Management. He went on to work for Tesco Stores as a Customer Service manager in Trowbridge, and later at Greystoke Properties in London as a Site Supervisor.</p>\r\n<p>His passion for football earned him a position as a &lsquo;Centre forward&rsquo; for Trowbridge Athletic FC where an unfortunate injury helped him discover a passion for teaching. He currently teaches IGCSE Economics, Enterprise and Business Studies and is the Head of the Humanities and Social Sciences Department.</p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 21:56:23','2015-02-21 21:56:23','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(11,'John','Kekeli Letsu','Chemistry Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-011.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>With a degree in Chemical Engineering from the Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST), John Kekeli Letsu teaches Chemistry in the Secondary School Science Department.</p>\r\n<p>Prior to teaching, he gained over three years&rsquo; industrial experience with The Council for Scientific and Industrial Research (CSIR), the United Nations Industrial Development Organisation (UNIDO, Ghana) and lastly the German Technical Cooperation (Gtz) as a Research Assistant.</p>\r\n<p>He loves young people and derives great joy and fulfilment from helping students, especially weaker ones, achieve academic excellence in the sciences.</p>\r\n<p>Kekeli, as he is popularly called, is single and lives in Batsona, off the Spintex Road.</p>\r\n<p>He enjoys listening to classical music and hymns. As leisure activities, he plays tennis and watches movies.</p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 22:00:02','2015-02-21 22:00:02','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(12,'Boudour','Obeid','Arabic Program Coordinator','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-004.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Boudour Obeid is the Arabic Programme Coordinator. Born and raised in Lebanon, she describes herself as a passionate educator with a special connection to the Arabic language. She is deeply committed to ensuring every student acquires close knowledge of the language. Spending many hours researching new advances and pedagogical methods, she explores Arabic materials used in other parts of the world for possible introduction to the ARIS classroom. She is very enthusiastic about encouraging students to incorporate Arabic into their daily lives, because only in this way will they learn to appreciate the true value of familiarity with the language and fluent proficiency in its use.</p>\r\n<p>Boudour enjoys reading and undertaking online research into education to add to her immeasurable collection of books and articles. Her daily routine is never complete without her morning cup of coffee while listening to the music of the famous Lebanese legend Fairuz.</p>','Administration','2015-02-21 22:05:08','2015-02-21 22:05:08','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Ms.',4),(13,'Frederick','Oppong-Boadi','Global Perspective Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-007.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Frederick Oppong-Boadi has a degree in Geography and Development from the Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST). He recently completed a Post Graduate Diploma in Education (PGDE) from the University of Education, Winneba.</p>\r\n<p>Fred (as he prefers) started his teaching in a local primary school in 2003 but left two years later to attend college. After working as a forestry officer for a large multinational mining corporation in Obuasi for two years, he changed career and started teaching full time in an inclusive school in 2010. Fred joined ARIS Secondary School in 2014 to teach Geography and History to Years 7 and 9, and has since trained to teach Humanities in the IB Diploma Programme. He has a huge passion for providing fun and enjoyable learning for his students.</p>\r\n<p>Fred is very proud to be part of the ARIS faculty and feels privileged to have the opportunity to work with such a diverse range of happy, hardworking and talented students. In his spare time you\'ll find him up a mountain, on a football pitch, in the gym, cooking...you get the general idea!</p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 22:07:52','2015-02-21 22:07:52','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(14,'Ali','Abubakar Siddik','Biology Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-017.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Ali Abubakar Siddik graduated from the University of Professional Studies, Legon. Having given much thought to the career directions he might take, he chose to apply to ARIS because it promised the best environment for his professional development. Ali has now been working as a teacher in the ARIS Science Department since October 2010. He entered the field because he has the passion and gift for not only teaching students but also for inspiring them, and guiding them into becoming productive citizens who have a love for learning.</p>\r\n<p>Ali is very patient and loves the excitement of being able to incorporate into his teaching diverse types of resources (such as books, digital media, music, art and movies) and bringing different experiences into the classroom. These experiences become part of the lives of some special people, ie ARIS students. Ali believes that being a facilitator in that process is a privilege that teachers enjoy much more than people in other walks of life.</p>\r\n<p>As a lifelong learner, Ali wishes to further his education, not only for the knowledge that he will gain from new courses, but also for the experience that life has to offer. During his four years at ARIS he has participated in Professional Development courses and other forms of training. These activities mean that he has to be confident, approachable, polite, reflective and an inquirer. Ali feels these are characteristics that will enable him to get involved with student life at any school in which he may work. Ambitions are to participate in conferences, in volunteer work both local and abroad, Webinars, INSETs and so on, thereby to enrich his experience. He feels confident he is on the right path.</p>\r\n<p>For recreation, Ali loves travelling, playing football and spending time with family and friends.</p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 22:10:05','2015-02-21 22:10:05','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(15,'Dorinda','Tham','English / Global Perspective Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-022.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>With four years in the classroom and a passion for inspiring children, Dorinda Tham teaches English Language and IGCSE Global Perspectives. It is extremely rewarding, she feels, to see how confident and enthusiastic students become when one can make them realize what they cannot see in themselves.</p>\r\n<p>Dorinda believes that learning should not just be about academics and scholarship but is also about developing and harnessing creativity, self-confidence and a sense of purpose. One of her favorite quotes is by Barbara Januszkiewicz: &ldquo;Creative thinking inspires ideas. Ideas inspire change.&rdquo; Dorinda believes that the moment teachers create the right learning environment to spark curiosity and self-confidence, they are half-way to developing creative thinkers; students who desire to make a difference no matter how small.</p>\r\n<p>On the last day of school, she can be found on the football field tackling the ball for her team.</p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 22:12:40','2015-02-21 22:12:40','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Ms.',0),(16,'Juliana','Mensah','Chemistry Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-001.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 22:25:25','2015-02-21 22:25:25','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Ms.',0),(17,'Samuel','Bonney','Art Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-005.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 22:26:02','2015-02-21 22:26:02','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(18,'Andrew','Adjeh Sowah','Art Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-006.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','2015-02-21 22:26:54','2015-02-21 22:26:54','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(19,'Trevor','Trumper','Head of Secondary','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-008.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Administration','2015-02-21 22:28:23','2015-02-21 22:28:23','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',3),(20,'Reina','Hamoui','H.R. & Administrator','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-009.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Administration','2015-02-21 22:31:19','2015-02-22 13:37:45','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Ms.',6),(21,'Daniel','Asante','ICT Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-013.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','2015-02-22 12:46:17','2015-02-22 12:46:17','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(22,'Benjamin-Tee','Sowah','ICT Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-014.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','2015-02-22 12:47:22','2015-02-22 12:47:22','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(23,'Victoria','Budu','English Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-015.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','2015-02-22 12:48:05','2015-02-22 12:48:05','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Ms.',0),(24,'Doris','Adu Bekoe','Receptionist','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-016.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Staff','2015-02-22 12:49:33','2015-02-22 12:49:33','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Ms.',0),(25,'Emanuel','Forson','Mathemathics Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-019.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','2015-02-22 12:53:27','2015-02-22 12:53:27','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0),(26,'Katherine','Tetteh','Librarian','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-020.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Staff','2015-02-22 12:56:09','2015-02-22 12:56:09','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com'